                <pb n="1"/>
            <p><hi rend="underline">THE CHAUTAUQUA SYSTEM OF EDUCATION</hi>.<lb/>
                THE CHAUTAUQUA LITERARY AND SCIENTIFIC CIRCLE.<lb/>
                DEPARTMENT OF JEWISH STUDIES.<lb/>
                COMMITTE ON ORGANIZATION<lb/>
                HENRY BERKOWITZ&#44; Chairman.	CHAS. S. BERNHEIMER.	SIMON MILLER.<lb/>
                JOSEPH KRAUSKOPF.	MAYER SULZBERGER.	MAX HERZBERG.<lb/>
                LEWIS W. STEINBACH.	MRS. CH. HEIDELBERGER.	CLINTON O. MAYER&#44; Rec. Secretary.<lb/>
                ISAAC HASSLER&#44; Cor. Secretary.		P. O. Box&#44; 825&#44;<lb/></p>
            <p>PHILADELPHIA&#44; PA.&#44; Mch. 26&#45;97<lb/></p>
            <p>Rev. Dr. S. Morais&#44;<lb/>
                Pres. of the Theolog&#45;<lb/>ical Seminary.<lb/>
                Dear Doctor&#59;&#45;<lb/></p>
            <p>The Jewish Chautauqua Society has determined upon an experiment in<lb/> the form of a Summer School and Assembly to be held in Atlantic City at<lb/> the end of July and first of August for two weeks.  It is our purpose to<lb/> endeavor to unify all the forces and organizations which are seeking to<lb/> promote Jewish education.  We would like to have you say something in<lb/> behalf of the Seminary at the opening. night.  A brief address bringing<lb/> forward the <sic>cuase</sic> you represent would be most welcome.  If not asking too<lb/> much we would be most happy to have you present&#44; or someone delegated by<lb/> you.  As we are desirous of issuing a prospectus as speedily as possible&#44;<lb/> an early reply will be very much appreciated by&#44;<lb/> Yours faithfully&#44;<lb/> Henry Berkowitz<lb/> Chancellor&#44;<lb/> Isaac Hassler&#44; Sec&#39;y.<lb/></p>
            <p>If you desire further information in regard to this movement&#44; I shall<lb/> be glad to see you personally.<lb/></p>
            </body>
